The maker of the Camry sedan and Prius hybrid said net profit came in at $17 billion in the year to March 31, down 24.5% from the year before, which was its best-ever result. The firm forecast net profit to rise 19.5%. For the current year to March 2020, Toyota expects operating profit will increase 3.3% Satoru Takada, an analyst at TIW, a Tokyo-based research and consulting firm, said "Toyota has cruised steadily, compared with its rivals." "The firm largely showed a reasonable performance around the world at a time when the global market is slowing down," he said. --AFP--